 formation theory to ethnographic research, this study reveals how a school racializes its students. But students are not just passive victims of such structural forces. They also creatively shape the way in which race is organized, imagined, and experienced.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362570940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503625709423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503625709/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles